This means that hearing the alarm is a requirement for contacting the authorities who can help save your home in an emergency. If you're not home to hear your alarm go off, it is effectively useless during times when you are away. The same applies to smart home security, which we cover <a href="https://ideaing.com/ideas/smart-home-security">here</a>.

Enter the smart home technology solution to air monitoring: smart Smoke &amp; Air Monitors.

&nbsp;

<strong>What Are Smart Smoke and Air Monitors?</strong>

These are devices which connect with your smartphone, usually via Wi-Fi, to update you about changes to your home's air quality and in some cases, even allow for remote control.

