How concerned should you be about home safety? In the FBI's most recent report on crime in the United States, over 1.7 million burglaries were reported annually and over 70% of those incidents took place on residential properties. Burglary is a legitimate problem, and one that hopefully you'll never have to experience. However, an ounce of prevention can go a long way in giving you peace of mind and in keeping predators from accessing your home.`

When my husband and I moved into our first house after years of apartment living, learning about home security quickly became an important priority. As exciting as it was to move into a bigger space, and to have more privacy, that came with losing our doorman and the security of having neighbors right down the hall! We've spent a lot of time researching options within the home security market, and were excited to see how many smart security products areÂ available today.

