This is a great solution for anyone who worries about their garage door as a security vulnerability. That concern is warranted considering how many break-ins begin with garages. This device would also work well in conjunction with a full-scale security system.

If you're looking for other ways to make your garage safer and more functional, read our article "<a href="https://ideaing.com/ideas/02/07/10-smart-garage-products-for-safety-organization" target="_blank">9 Gadgets You Need in Your Garage</a>."

&nbsp;
<h2 class="a-size-large a-spacing-none"></h2>
<h2 id="title" class="a-size-large a-spacing-none">Security Lighting</h2>
&nbsp;

Lighting may not seem like an important factor in security, but it is. As we've mentioned in this article, one of the biggest factors in your home security system is its visibility. You want potential threats to see that your home is well-protected before they ever try breaking in. The ideal situation is that an attempted break-in never happens, because you home seems too difficult to access.

A well-lit home does several things to make your home look impenetrable:
<ul>
 	<li>A lit home looks occupied. Most burglars don't want to break into a home where people are home.</li>
 	<li>A lit home is easy for outsiders to see, which means that burglars have to worry about your neighbors seeing them committing this crime.</li>
</ul>
You have several options in smart home security lighting. The more technically advanced version involves lightbulbs or electrical outlets that you can turn on and off remotely through your smartphone. These systems can light your home from the inside and outside, making it truly appear that your family is home.

A less expensive, and easier to install, automated lighting system involves solar powered lights that automatically turn on when they sense motion. These are used outdoors, and have their own advantages and disadvantages. In the pro column: they're much less expensive and require almost no installation skills or upkeep. On the downside: they're often not as bright as larger lighting setups, and lighting your home from the inside can be more effective in convincing burglars that you are in the house.

