&nbsp;
<h2>Security Cameras</h2>
&nbsp;

Unfortunately, many seasoned burglars have "seen it all" Â when it comes to smart home security systems. They even know how to break through some of the professionally installed setups. Having a good camera setup changes the game in favor of the homeowner. If you can catch a thief in the act, or right before they break into your home, you have a huge piece of evidence against them.
<p style="text-align: left;">Wireless camera systems allow you to connect to your smartphone and monitor the activity around your home via your smartphone 24/7. These systems also allow you to save all of your video footage to a cloud account where you can review it if necessary.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">As far as camera placement, a good rule of thumb is that any area where you've chosen to place a sensor would also benefit from a single camera. So, if you've attached a sensor to both your front door and windows, you could also include one camera to monitor that entire front entryway area.</p>
